name: Scotland vs Hungary
summary: Scotland's Euro 2024 hopes were dashed as they succumbed to a 1-0 defeat against Hungary in a crucial Group A encounter. Despite being favored pre-match, the Scots failed to find the back of the net and had a dismal record of only one shot on target throughout the entire match. Hungary's triumph was secured by Kevin Csoboth's well-timed goal, further emphasizing Scotland's disappointing performance. The result eliminated Scotland from the tournament and left Hungary in a favorable position to advance.
